                Bhadrachalam is a famous pilgrimage town located in the state of Telangana, India. It is situated on the banks of the Godavari River amidst picturesque landscapes. <br>

Best Time to Visit- October to March <br>
Ideal Vacation Duration- 1-2 days <br>
Average expenses: Starting from ₹15,000 (2 days/1 night) <br>
Places to Visit- Bhadrachalam Temple, Parnasala, Abhaya Anjaneya Temple, Godavari River Ghat. <br>
Things to Do- Attend the daily rituals at Bhadrachalam Temple, take a boat ride on the Godavari River, explore the surrounding natural beauty, experience the local culture and traditions. <br>
Gopanna (1620 - 1680), popularly known as Bhadradri Ramadasu or Bhadrachala Ramadasu, was a 17th-century Indian devotee of Rama and a composer of Carnatic music. His devotional lyrics to Rama are famous in South Indian classical music as Ramadaasu Keertanalu, and have made Bhadrachalam a place of religious importance for Hindus. <br>


